Previously we saw how the get() method can be used to get elements from a particular position. There is another method **`indexOf()`** which is used to find the index of an element

```
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.Collections; 

ArrayList seed-it = new ArrayList<();
codechef.add(45);
codechef.add(56);
codechef.add(23);

codechef.indexOf(56) // This will return the position of the element 56
```
### Task
You are given $T$ test cases
- the 1st line of each test case are 2 integers - $N$ and $X$
- the 2nd line of each test case contains $N$ space separated integers which form the list $A$

For each list $A$ - you need to output the following $2$ integers on a single line
- the occurrence of $X$ in the list $A$
- the index or the position where $X$ occurs for the 1st time in the list $A$

**Note:** Lists in Java are zero indexed. Hence index() of the 1st element will be $0$.

